context: <a0_0><b3_0>EU member countries<b3_0/><a0_0/> have shown support for ambitious renewable energy goals. In 2010, <a1_0><b4_0><b5_0>Eurobarometer<b5_0/><b4_0/><a1_0/> polled the twenty-seven EU member states about the target "to increase the share of renewable energy in the EU by 20 percent by <a2_0><b6_0>2020<b6_0/><a2_0/>". Most people in all twenty-seven countries either approved of the target or called for it to go further. Across the EU, 57 percent thought the proposed goal was "about right" and 16 percent thought it was "too modest." In comparison, 19 percent said it was "too ambitious".
